  "_comment": "Real context windows for locally-served models reached via openai/<tag> through ollama-spec-proxy at /v1. Without this aider falls back to its tiny default (~4k tokens) and silently drops files. For ollama-served tags each entry matches the model's PARAMETER num_ctx (set by the rebuild script in this repo). NOTE: tags the proxy routes to a vLLM backend (substring match on VLLM_BACKENDS) are instead capped by that service's --max-model-len, which is LOWER than the GGUF's num_ctx: 'codestral*' and anything containing 'qwen3-32b'/'qwen3:32b' (incl. hf.co/unsloth/Qwen3-32B-GGUF) hit vLLM's 32768 on the 32GB card, so their totals are 32768 here even though ollama could do more on fallback. max_input_tokens = effective_ctx - max_output_tokens, leaving headroom for the model's reply.",
